<article>
    <h1>Safe work&#xAD;place tips for Phase 2</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200918/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-18"><time>2020-09-18</time></a>
        - <span>CLASSIFIED&#xAD;S</span>
        - <span role="byline">By Arul John</span>
    </section>

    <p>As Phase 2 has come into ef­fect, many work­places that had to shut down tem­po­rar­ily or im­ple­ment work from home sched­ules are now be­gin­ning to re­sume work­place op­er­a­tions. Take note of these tips when re­turn­ing to the work­place.</p>
    <p>• Wher­ever pos­si­ble, con­tinue to prac­tise safe dis­tanc­ing to limit the spread of COVID-19. Check out the safe dis­tanc­ing mea­sures im­ple­mented at your work­place and fol­low them for your and your col­leagues’ safety.</p>
    <p>• Re­view the Busi­ness Con­ti­nu­ity Plan (BCP) de­signed to min­imise dis­rup­tions to busi­ness op­er­a­tions and en­sure that busi­nesses remain vi­able dur­ing the out­break. • Re­duce phys­i­cal in­ter­ac­tion as much as pos­si­ble and nec­es­sary. Pay spe­cial at­ten­tion to vul­ner­a­ble em­ploy­ees such as the el­derly and preg­nant, as well as those with un­der­ly­ing med­i­cal con­di­tions. • Where nec­es­sary, talk to your su­pe­ri­ors about re­view­ing work pro­cesses and the IT equip­ment and fa­cil­i­ties re­quired.</p>
    <p>• Look into whether that face-to-face meet­ing is al­ways needed and check on how to re­duce the num­ber of meet­ings, at­ten­dees at each meet­ing and the du­ra­tions.</p>
    <p>• Work sta­tions and seats in meet­ing rooms should be spaced at least 1 me­tre apart. This should also ap­ply to com­mon spa­ces, such as en­trances and ex­its, lifts, can­teens and pantries.</p>
    <p>• Where pos­si­ble, sug­gest stag­gered work­ing hours to re­duce the pos­si­ble con­gre­ga­tion of em­ploy­ees at com­mon spa­ces. • De­fer non-crit­i­cal events and scale down crit­i­cal ones</p>
    <p>• Main­tain reg­u­lar tem­per­a­ture/ health screen­ing and on­line reg­is­tra­tion.</p>
    <p>• Im­prove ven­ti­la­tion and in­crease the fre­quency of clean­ing of ar­eas with high hu­man con­tact, such as com­mon spa­ces, toi­lets, lifts and handrails</p>
    <p>• Ob­tain travel dec­la­ra­tions from em­ploy­ees on travel his­tory and up­com­ing travel plans.</p>


</article>

